0-25 minutes, which is a pretty short duration.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.13874,0.21816,0.16865,0.098909,0.069102,0.07042,0.051391,0.059401,0.038787,0.034969,0.027417,0.024047],"unified_progress":[0.12686,0.14863,0.11694,0.1087,0.082644,0.085236,0.068514,0.078723,0.057857,0.051232,0.041952,0.032709]},{"section":5,"text":"She's worried about having more of these, which makes sense because they sound really intense.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.11689,0.17716,0.14372,0.10233,0.080713,0.081106,0.06302,0.067394,0.049563,0.04708,0.037427,0.033598],"unified_progress":[0.11673,0.12431,0.10412,0.10022,0.086803,0.088791,0.075724,0.082326,0.065762,0.062438,0.051494,0.041284]},{"section":6,"text":"First, I need to think about what conditions present with panic attacks.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.09384,0.12456,0.12783,0.11975,0.09983,0.078998,0.072509,0.067046,0.056186,0.066485,0.046371,0.046589],"unified_progress":[0.11025,0.082658,0.084866,0.0962,0.0948,0.088751,0.088615,0.085689,0.074658,0.083107,0.061541,0.048869]},{"section":7,"text":"The symptoms listed\u2014sweating, palpitations, derealization (which is feeling detached from the surroundings), and the fear of future episodes\u2014are classic for panic disorder.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.083732,0.13376,0.11165,0.097776,0.091008,0.089399,0.080193,0.080283,0.066054,0.062867,0.054198,0.049073],"unified_progress":[0.078121,0.10214,0.098198,0.090075,0.089965,0.093135,0.086295,0.090731,0.07905,0.075199,0.064397,0.052695]},{"section":8,"text":"The duration of 20-25 minutes also fits because panic attacks typically peak around 10 minutes but can last up to an hour.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.077485,0.12158,0.10826,0.09575,0.090456,0.089997,0.083059,0.082924,0.070682,0.068329,0.058117,0.053362],"unified_progress":[0.083702,0.093243,0.093515,0.092068,0.090346,0.093318,0.087572,0.08969,0.08011,0.07682,0.065453,0.054163]},{"section":9,"text":"The fact that all routine investigations are normal is important.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056054,0.1034,0.1105,0.10479,0.096272,0.090357,0.085019,0.081745,0.07535,0.075313,0.064291,0.056908],"unified_progress":[0.052695,0.087263,0.090662,0.097605,0.097768,0.095011,0.093087,0.090058,0.08494,0.084759,0.070994,0.055157]},{"section":10,"text":"That rules out things like hyperthyroidism, pheochromocytoma, or other medical causes that can mimic anxiety attacks.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040579,0.082683,0.095993,0.10151,0.1019,0.098915,0.096468,0.090733,0.083127,0.08154,0.06888,0.057668],"unified_progress":[0.039729,0.071603,0.08741,0.095157,0.099374,0.10258,0.10048,0.096779,0.09142,0.088254,0.072849,0.054371]},{"section":11,"text":"For example, if her thyroid function tests were abnormal, that could be a cause.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038626,0.080058,0.09428,0.09896,0.098818,0.097017,0.096333,0.092372,0.087061,0.083483,0.073482,0.059509],"unified_progress":[0.046596,0.078521,0.089317,0.095276,0.099562,0.09757,0.098065,0.094389,0.089359,0.085779,0.0721,0.053466]},{"section":12,"text":"But since they're normal, it's more likely a primary psychiatric condition.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040192,0.081549,0.097552,0.10106,0.097057,0.090924,0.089511,0.086174,0.08202,0.085172,0.074553,0.074231],"unified_progress":[0.044466,0.073064,0.082233,0.092492,0.093349,0.091945,0.095222,0.092086,0.088996,0.091314,0.082338,0.072495]},{"section":13,"text":"Derealization is a dissociative symptom often seen in panic attacks.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03718,0.073018,0.084807,0.093929,0.099237,0.098965,0.099209,0.094332,0.087489,0.087117,0.076058,0.06866],"unified_progress":[0.049629,0.06372,0.079086,0.08786,0.094025,0.10188,0.098858,0.098423,0.09375,0.091284,0.077953,0.063531]},{"section":14,"text":"The fear of future attacks might lead to agoraphobia, but the main issue here is the panic attacks themselves.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043743,0.081854,0.085209,0.087598,0.09072,0.093587,0.094188,0.093662,0.088624,0.087168,0.07955,0.074098],"unified_progress":[0.048443,0.069518,0.07575,0.081719,0.087121,0.093687,0.093074,0.096475,0.095158,0.095226,0.088242,0.075585]},{"section":15,"text":"Other possibilities to consider: maybe a generalized anxiety disorder, but that's more about chronic anxiety rather than discrete episodes.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031269,0.066735,0.081188,0.088842,0.093029,0.093682,0.098085,0.098528,0.095294,0.096426,0.086346,0.070575],"unified_progress":[0.034012,0.061526,0.07578,0.086145,0.09253,0.094865,0.099111,0.10127,0.099599,0.10356,0.087736,0.063867]},{"section":16,"text":"Social anxiety disorder?","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026,0.060356,0.074555,0.084309,0.092787,0.097581,0.10314,0.10451,0.10106,0.098755,0.089428,0.067515],"unified_progress":[0.048813,0.062567,0.075658,0.084374,0.092254,0.095907,0.099615,0.10265,0.099403,0.10028,0.082176,0.0563]},{"section":17,"text":"But the episodes happen anytime, not just in social situations.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029929,0.06412,0.072954,0.080031,0.08765,0.094788,0.10213,0.10556,0.10325,0.099539,0.092567,0.067484],"unified_progress":[0.054464,0.065858,0.074254,0.080012,0.08975,0.092982,0.096718,0.1033,0.10084,0.10403,0.08389,0.053899]},{"section":18,"text":"PTSD could have panic-like symptoms, but there's no mention of trauma here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.019886,0.050229,0.065623,0.077197,0.086374,0.09455,0.10584,0.1105,0.11017,0.10855,0.10113,0.069946],"unified_progress":[0.029205,0.055775,0.069849,0.078857,0.091321,0.095257,0.10171,0.1092,0.10922,0.11551,0.091578,0.052515]},{"section":19,"text":"Also, considering the sudden onset and the cluster of symptoms, panic disorder is the most straightforward diagnosis.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031761,0.069103,0.085836,0.09147,0.090378,0.086996,0.088718,0.08854,0.087632,0.097486,0.088091,0.093988],"unified_progress":[0.033095,0.058277,0.06974,0.081976,0.085752,0.089376,0.102,0.095692,0.095367,0.102,0.096949,0.089779]},{"section":20,"text":"The key differentiator from a heart attack or other medical crisis is the normal investigations and the episodic nature.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028571,0.064261,0.079308,0.086665,0.090314,0.091753,0.09617,0.097124,0.096386,0.097847,0.091455,0.080147],"unified_progress":[0.031119,0.057845,0.071235,0.080589,0.088597,0.092736,0.09761,0.10158,0.1022,0.10688,0.094742,0.074879]},{"section":21,"text":"Since the tests are normal, we can be more confident it's not a medical issue.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033305,0.067703,0.080542,0.086275,0.088272,0.088781,0.091481,0.092074,0.091974,0.094135,0.089707,0.095751],"unified_progress":[0.03771,0.059176,0.068939,0.077485,0.082647,0.086517,0.09148,0.094101,0.096009,0.10057,0.10236,0.10301]},{"section":22,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is panic disorder.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030995,0.054326,0.062726,0.068702,0.073235,0.076515,0.08207,0.086135,0.092591,0.098602,0.10842,0.16568],"unified_progress":[0.031654,0.036096,0.043761,0.053336,0.058335,0.06812,0.073285,0.084745,0.096317,0.10833,0.14552,0.20051]},{"section":23,"text":"The patient's symptoms align perfectly with recurrent unexpected panic attacks, along with worry about future attacks, which is part of the diagnostic criteria.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":f